---
By: Plato
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 103
    Verse: 5
Tags:
  - Devil
---
When a man is always occupied with the cravings of desire and ambition, and
is eagerly striving to satisfy them, all his thoughts must be mortal.
...But he who has been earnest in the love of knowledge and wisdom. ...must
have thoughts immortal and divine.
